Run the model on a NeuronCore via `torch-neuronx` / `torch_xla`: place tensors on the XLA device (`import torch_xla.core.xla_model as xm; device = xm.xla_device()`) with an efficient dtype (`torch.bfloat16`). Do NOT run inference on CPU or in `float32` — it will be far too slow. NeuronCores execute compiled graphs, so call `xm.mark_step()` (or trace/compile with `torch_neuronx.trace`) to materialize work on the device; never leave the hot path running eagerly on CPU. The first compile (`neuronx-cc`) of each new graph shape takes minutes — reuse the persistent compile cache and keep shapes static so later steps hit the cache instead of recompiling.
